# nim-proxy container-level config. Everything else — NIM keys, client API
# keys, the open/keyed API mode, users, limits, pricing, history retention, the
# model-pressure governor — is configured in the dashboard on first run (a
# setup wizard) and stored in DATA_DIR/config.json. Legacy app-level env vars
# (NIM_API_KEYS, PROXY_API_KEYS, ADMIN_PASSWORD, INSECURE_NO_AUTH, …) are
# ignored, with a one-line boot warning if any are still set.

# Bind address / port the proxy listens on.
#HOST=0.0.0.0
#PORT=8000

# Where the config store and history.jsonl live. The Docker image sets /data
# (volume-backed). Must be writable — an unwritable dir is a hard boot error
# (the store holds credentials). Outside Docker it defaults to ./data.
#DATA_DIR=data

# Set true when a reverse proxy / platform terminates TLS in front of you: the
# session cookie is then marked Secure (requires X-Forwarded-Proto: https).
#TRUST_PROXY=false

# Log verbosity, e.g. nim_proxy=debug
#RUST_LOG=nim_proxy=info
